This paper deals with the design and analysis of communication networks for real-time distributed embedded systems, which is a topic closely related to computer networks (cs.NI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves the use of probabilistic models and Markov chains to analyze the performance of the network, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the computational complexity of the scoring problem, which is a topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR).
